OBLIGATIONS CARRIED FORWARD
---------------------------
Because the source is a U.S. Government work not subject to domestic copyright, NO
attribution, non-commercial, or share-alike obligation attaches to it. The content of
this pack may therefore be reproduced, transformed, and redistributed freely, including
commercially. As a courtesy (not an obligation):
  - Attribution to NIST is provided in PACK.yaml and throughout the pack.
  - NIST does not endorse this pack; nothing here should be read as a NIST endorsement.
  - "NIST" and the publication identifier are used nominatively to identify the source.

THIRD-PARTY CAVEAT
------------------
SP 800-37 Rev 2 references and adopts material owned by others — notably the
ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288 engineering definition of a "system," and it points to companion NIST
and federal documents (SP 800-53 and SP 800-53B control catalog/baselines, FIPS 199/200
and CNSSI 1253 categorization, SP 800-39/30/137/161). This pack SYNTHESIZES the RMF
process in original words and does NOT reproduce the SP 800-53 control catalog or its
baselines, the FIPS/CNSSI impact tables, or any long verbatim ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288 process
text. Those works remain governed by their respective publishers' terms (ISO/IEC/IEEE
material is third-party copyrighted; the other NIST/FIPS documents are themselves U.S.
Government works).

